description:
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Working hours: 37.5 hours per week&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are looking for an enthusiastic, self-motivated and flexible individual to join the Senior Infrastructure Specialist Team as a Senior Technician for Core Infrastructure. As a Senior Technician you will be involved with delivery and support of servers both physical &amp; virtual, storage, backups and a wide variety of general infrastructure solutions. The candidate will ideally be qualified to degree level in a relevant field, be in possession of a suitable Microsoft qualification such as MCP / MCSE or have demonstrable equivalent knowledge and experience. Participation in out of hours service management rota will be required and the role may include participation in the on-call rota.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The candidate must possess&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Intermediate working knowledge of a range of major IT infrastructure service systems such as but not limited to server / desktop virtualisation technologies, DNS, DHCP, SAN, SQL, IIS, SCCM and Citrix.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Intermediate working and understanding of current Microsoft server operating system environments.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Skills and experience in scripting &amp; process automation.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience in Azure cloud architecture&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Desirable skills&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Exposure to open source software(s)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;SharePoint system management.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This is a great opportunity to really develop your skills in a dynamic environment. The successful candidate will demonstrate use of their own judgement on several general support issues whilst adhering to department protocols, referring to peers and understanding when it is appropriate to implement escalation processes and have the ability to run projects on their own or with a team.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You must be forward thinking, capable of assisting in the design of the long term technical strategy to provide value &amp; benefit to the organisation. Good communication and interpersonal skills are necessary as well as the ability to explain complex technical solutions at all levels.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Name Paul Keith&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Job title Senior IT Specialist / Architect - Core Infrastructure&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Email address paul.keith@nhs.net&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Telephone number 01244 362372&lt;/p&gt;
